; Test for issue #1221: Null pointer dereference in apply_tag_directive
; The original bug was a crash when apply_tag_directive was called with
; a NULL pointer, causing a SEGV in strlen via trim_ws.  The fix added
; null checks to all apply_*_directive functions.
;
; NOTE: The crash scenario (missing argument) cannot be tested here
; because it would cause ledger to exit with an error, and the journal
; data from the error case would not parse for subsequent test blocks.
; This test verifies that valid apply tag usage works correctly after
; the null-check fix.

; Valid usage: apply tag with argument should work correctly
apply tag Important

2024/01/01 Test transaction
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

end apply

test reg
24-Jan-01 Test transaction      Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0
end test

; Verify that balances are correct after applying the tag
test bal --no-total
             $-10.00  Assets:Cash
              $10.00  Expenses:Food
end test
